column5: Just got 20 walleye and a 9.4lb sheep head in 4 hours and I popped an 8 pound walter
Nice eye and pretty respectable sheephead too !!
nice!... that wally looks like your tossing an airplane...
Did you keep the sheepshead? Looks like picture is in a basement. Nice looking walter and nice boat too.
Nice looking walleye and thats a big sheephead to.
Nice job there to say the least!  If that's BOQ, that 8lb'r is an impressive catch this time of year for sure there!  Wow!  And that sheepy is a beast  good stuff
great day on the lake - Nice Walter
No... We didn't keep the sheepy... Caught it after dark and wanted a pic... That was in our boathouse
I was thinking the same thing ... " Do people eat those? " lol  Nice catch !!
I don't think so... But then again... Some people keep everything they catch... So some people must eat em...
that is one heck of a walleye!  Big sheephead as well  Cheers!

Nice eye!! Solid fish!   My buddy had Italo out on Lake George this past weekend. Although they caught walleye, they ended up keeping a sheepshead for dinner. Italo cut the meat into finger like strips and had the hotel cook the fish up for them.  My buddy said it was awesome and will be keeping another one in the future....  TDunn
My dad, and others I've heard, keep sheepies for chowder.  Apparently they are perfect for it.
